<TITLE> BNP meets CEC over constitution deadline </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com)Representatives of main opposition BNP on Thursday met with chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda over extension of the deadline for submitting the permanent constitution of the party. The meeting started at the Election Commission Secretariat at around 3:30pm. Vice-president MK Anwar led the BNP delegation that included joint secretary Nazrul Islam Khan and office secretary Rizvi Ahmed. Thirty-nine political parties submitted the draft constitution to the EC for registration before the ninth parliamentary elections for provisional registration. According to the Representation of the People Order political parties are to submit their constitutions after approval by national council within six months after the parliament convenes. The deadline for submission is July 25 but no political party has submitted their permanent constitutions yet. bd
